==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ossein
<hw>Os"se*in</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>os</ets>
bone.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol. Chem.)</fld> <def>The organic basis of bone
tissue; the residue after removal of the mineral matters from bone by
dilute acid; in embryonic tissue, the substance in which the mineral
salts are deposited to form bone; bone collagen; -- called also
<altname>ostein</altname>. Chemically it is the same as
<compof>collagen</compof>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Osselet</ent>⟦br⟧
